<figureCitation id="136EB693FFC2FF9322B690220C16B601" box="[1227,1359,845,869]" captionStart="FIGURES 30 – 35" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1776,1799]" captionTargetBox="[158,1428,186,1768]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,181,1768]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 30 – 35. Dasypolia spp., male genitalia. 30, D. templi, Russia, Altai Mts., Aktash, slide AV 0428 Volynkin; 31, D. templi, Russia, Altai Mts., Aktash, slide AV 0392 Volynkin; 32, D. maria, holotype, Russia, Altai Mts., Aktash, slide AV 0407 Volynkin; 33, D. maria, paratype, Russia, Altai Mts., Aktash, slide AV 0587 Volynkin; 34, D. akbar, holotype, Afghanistan, ZSM Genitalprp. 960 Boursin (photo by U. Buchsbaum); 35, D. melancholica, paratype, N India, Himachal Pradesh, Pr. 5382 Hacker, after Hacker &amp; Peks, 1992." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/282301/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="419">
Figs. 
<number id="3D9DB831FFC2FF93237490220C16B601" box="[1289,1359,845,869]" pageId="3" pageNumber="419" value="32.33">32, 33</number>
</figureCitation>
) differ from 
<taxonomicName id="4C55D195FFC2FF9326AA901E0864B6EC" box="[215,317,880,904]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Dasypolia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="419" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="akbar">
<emphasis id="B9217604FFC2FF9326AA901E0864B6EC" box="[215,317,880,904]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="419">D. akbar</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="136EB693FFC2FF932732900008FAB6E3" box="[335,419,879,903]" captionStart="FIGURES 30 – 35" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1776,1799]" captionTargetBox="[158,1428,186,1768]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,181,1768]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 30 – 35. Dasypolia spp., male genitalia. 30, D. templi, Russia, Altai Mts., Aktash, slide AV 0428 Volynkin; 31, D. templi, Russia, Altai Mts., Aktash, slide AV 0392 Volynkin; 32, D. maria, holotype, Russia, Altai Mts., Aktash, slide AV 0407 Volynkin; 33, D. maria, paratype, Russia, Altai Mts., Aktash, slide AV 0587 Volynkin; 34, D. akbar, holotype, Afghanistan, ZSM Genitalprp. 960 Boursin (photo by U. Buchsbaum); 35, D. melancholica, paratype, N India, Himachal Pradesh, Pr. 5382 Hacker, after Hacker &amp; Peks, 1992." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/282301/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="419">
Fig. 
<number id="3D9DB831FFC2FF9327FB900008FAB6E3" box="[390,419,879,903]" pageId="3" pageNumber="419" value="34.0">34</number>
</figureCitation>
) by shorter and basally wider uncus, wider juxta, slightly narrower valva, more massive digitus, longer harpe with medial loop strongly extending beyond the costa; from 
<taxonomicName id="4C55D195FFC2FF93226690FB0D88B6CF" box="[1051,1233,915,939]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Dasypolia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="419" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="melancholica">
<emphasis id="B9217604FFC2FF93226690FB0D88B6CF" box="[1051,1233,915,939]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="419">D. melancholica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it differs (
<figureCitation id="136EB693FFC2FF93233990FD0CCAB6CE" box="[1348,1427,914,938]" captionStart="FIGURES 30 – 35" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1776,1799]" captionTargetBox="[158,1428,186,1768]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,181,1768]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 30 – 35. Dasypolia spp., male genitalia. 30, D. templi, Russia, Altai Mts., Aktash, slide AV 0428 Volynkin; 31, D. templi, Russia, Altai Mts., Aktash, slide AV 0392 Volynkin; 32, D. maria, holotype, Russia, Altai Mts., Aktash, slide AV 0407 Volynkin; 33, D. maria, paratype, Russia, Altai Mts., Aktash, slide AV 0587 Volynkin; 34, D. akbar, holotype, Afghanistan, ZSM Genitalprp. 960 Boursin (photo by U. Buchsbaum); 35, D. melancholica, paratype, N India, Himachal Pradesh, Pr. 5382 Hacker, after Hacker &amp; Peks, 1992." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/282301/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="419">
Fig. 
<number id="3D9DB831FFC2FF93230A90FD0CCAB6CE" box="[1399,1427,914,938]" pageId="3" pageNumber="419" value="35.0">35</number>
</figureCitation>
) by shorter and basally wider uncus, wider juxta, narrower valva, more massive digitus, slightly shorter harpe with anterior loop strongly extending beyond the costa and distal part not extending over the lateral margin of valva.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34FF99DFFC2FF9326BA90950A08B33B" pageId="3" pageNumber="419" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BEAAA16FFC2FF9326BA90950DBBB093" blockId="3.[151,1436,602,1667]" pageId="3" pageNumber="419">
<emphasis id="B9217604FFC2FF9326BA90950800B177" bold="true" box="[199,345,1018,1043]" pageId="3" pageNumber="419">Description.</emphasis>
External morphology (
<figureCitation id="136EB693FFC2FF93241B90950B81B176" box="[614,728,1018,1042]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 10" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1844,1867]" captionTargetBox="[174,1414,187,1832]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[173,1417,187,1833]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 10. Dasypolia and Tholera spp., adults. 1, Dasypolia templi, male, Russia, Altai Mts., Aktash [AVB]; 2, D. templi, male, Russia, Altai Mts., Aktash [AVB]; 3, D. templi, female, Russia, Altai Mts., Aktash [AVB]; 4, D. templi, female, Russia, Altai Mts., Tigireksky Ridge [AVB]; 5, D. maria, male, holotype, Russia, Altai Mts., Aktash [ZISP]; 6, D. maria, male, paratype, Russia, Altai Mts., Aktash [MČK]; 7, D. akbar, male, holotype, Afghanistan (photo by U. Buchsbaum) [ZSM]; 8, ditto, labels (Photo by U. Buchsbaum); 9, D. melancholica, female, paratype, N India, Himachal Pradesh, after Hacker &amp; Peks, 1992; 10, Tholera cespitis, male, Russia, Altai Mts., Aktash [AVB]." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/282298/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="419">
Figs. 
<number id="3D9DB831FFC2FF9324D590950B81B176" box="[680,728,1018,1042]" pageId="3" pageNumber="419" value="5.6">5, 6</number>
</figureCitation>
). Wingspan 
<quantity id="4CAD07F3FFC2FF93251490950ABEB176" box="[873,999,1018,1042]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.65" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="3.3" pageId="3" pageNumber="419" unit="mm" value="36.5" valueMax="40.0" valueMin="33.0">33–40 mm</quantity>
, length of forewing 
<quantity id="4CAD07F3FFC2FF9322AB90950C0DB176" box="[1238,1364,1018,1042]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.65" metricValueMax="1.8" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="3" pageNumber="419" unit="mm" value="16.5" valueMax="18.0" valueMin="15.0">15–18 mm</quantity>
. Male antennae serrate and fasciculate. Labial palps short, porrect. Head, thorax and abdomen olive brown. Ground colour of forewing olive brown. Antemedial and postmedial lines thin, dark; antemedial line strongly dentate; postmedial line repandodentate. Subterminal line wavy, dentate, pale, diffused. Terminal line dark, thin, poorly defined. Medial area strongly darkened. Terminal area slightly paler than subterminal. Orbicular pale, very small; reniform small, pale, oval, with dark reniform nucleus. Cilia brownish grey. Hindwing brownish grey. Medial line broad, strongly diffused, grey. Discal spot dark, semilunar, thin. Male genitalia (
<figureCitation id="136EB693FFC2FF93222797A50DB7B186" box="[1114,1262,1226,1250]" captionStart="FIGURES 30 – 35" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1776,1799]" captionTargetBox="[158,1428,186,1768]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,181,1768]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 30 – 35. Dasypolia spp., male genitalia. 30, D. templi, Russia, Altai Mts., Aktash, slide AV 0428 Volynkin; 31, D. templi, Russia, Altai Mts., Aktash, slide AV 0392 Volynkin; 32, D. maria, holotype, Russia, Altai Mts., Aktash, slide AV 0407 Volynkin; 33, D. maria, paratype, Russia, Altai Mts., Aktash, slide AV 0587 Volynkin; 34, D. akbar, holotype, Afghanistan, ZSM Genitalprp. 960 Boursin (photo by U. Buchsbaum); 35, D. melancholica, paratype, N India, Himachal Pradesh, Pr. 5382 Hacker, after Hacker &amp; Peks, 1992." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/282301/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="419">
Figs. 
<number id="3D9DB831FFC2FF9322E297A50DB7B186" box="[1183,1262,1226,1250]" pageId="3" pageNumber="419" value="32.33">32, 33</number>
</figureCitation>
). Uncus short, moderately long, obtuse apically. Tegumen short, rather broad, with small penicular lobes. Juxta strongly sclerotized, broad, subdeltoidal, apically with deep incision; lateral lobes with long and slender apical processes; medial apical process moderately long, rather broad. Vinculum rather short, massive, V-shaped. Valva broad, rather short; cucculus large, broad, apically rounded, dorsally curved. Costal process long, broad, massive, apically narrowed. Clavus small, rounded, setose. Harpe very long, narrow, basally slightly broadened, apically rounded, Sshaped, with proximal loop strongly extending beyond the costa. Aedeagus tubular, rather narrow, almost straight; carina with strongly sclerotized finely dentate dorsal plate. Vesica narrow, tubular, membranous, dorsally curved, with short and broad ventral diverticulum and two very small dorsal diverticuli. Female unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEAAA16FFC2FF9326BA956D0A08B33B" blockId="3.[151,1436,602,1667]" pageId="3" pageNumber="419">
<emphasis id="B9217604FFC2FF9326BA956D0B5BB37F" bold="true" box="[199,514,1538,1563]" pageId="3" pageNumber="419">Bionomics &amp; Distribuition</emphasis>
. The species has been collected in dry habitats on steppe rocky slopes with bushes at medium altitudes (
<figureCitation id="136EB693FFC2FF9327F4954A0887B359" box="[393,478,1573,1597]" captionStart="FIGURES 54 – 55. 54" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1937,1960]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,291,1925]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,291,1928]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 54 – 55. 54, Map of type localities of Dasypolia: orange point— D. tuektiensis, green point— D. bubnovae, blue point — D. maria; 55, Collecting site: vicinity of Aktash, Aigulaksky Ridge. Type locality of D. maria and locality of D. templi, D. lama and D. tuektiensis." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/282305/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="419">
Fig. 
<number id="3D9DB831FFC2FF9327C2954A0887B359" box="[447,478,1573,1597]" pageId="3" pageNumber="419" value="55.0">55</number>
</figureCitation>
). The species is known only from the 
<typeStatus id="54EE14B4FFC2FF9325DD95490A89B35A" box="[928,976,1574,1598]" pageId="3" pageNumber="419">type</typeStatus>
locality, the southern macroslope of the Aigulaksky Ridge near the Aktash village in the Central Altai.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34FF99DFFC2FF9326BA95040DB7B3E6" box="[199,1262,1642,1667]" pageId="3" pageNumber="419" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BEAAA16FFC2FF9326BA95040DB7B3E6" blockId="3.[151,1436,602,1667]" box="[199,1262,1642,1667]" pageId="3" pageNumber="419">
<emphasis id="B9217604FFC2FF9326BA9504081FB3E7" bold="true" box="[199,326,1643,1667]" pageId="3" pageNumber="419">Etymology</emphasis>
. The species name is dedicated to 
<taxonomicName id="4C55D195FFC2FF9324B695050A57B3E6" box="[715,782,1642,1666]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Dasypolia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="427" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maria">Maria</taxonomicName>
S. Ivanova, botanist and the author’s wife.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
